# StaffLink — A3 Installation Guide

## Environment

Tested on macOS (Darwin 21.6.0) and Ubuntu 24.04 LTS.

## Prerequisites

- Node.js 18+ (https://nodejs.org)
- npm 9+

---

## 1. Backend Setup

```bash
cd A3/backend
npm install
npx prisma migrate deploy   # Apply DB migrations
npm run seed                 # Seed the database with test data
npm start                    # Start backend on port 3000
```

The backend runs at http://localhost:3000

### Environment Variables (optional)

Create `A3/backend/.env`:
```
FRONTEND_URL=http://localhost:5173
```

---

## 2. Frontend Setup (Development)

```bash
cd A3/frontend
npm install
npm run dev          # Start dev server at http://localhost:5173
```

The frontend dev server talks to the backend at http://localhost:3000.

---

## 3. Frontend Build (Production)

```bash
cd A3/frontend
npm run build        # Outputs to dist/
```

---

## 4. Deployment

### Option A — Serve with Nginx (Ubuntu 24.04)

1. Install Nginx:
   ```bash
   sudo apt update && sudo apt install nginx -y
   ```

2. Build the frontend:
   ```bash
   cd A3/frontend && npm run build
   sudo cp -r dist/* /var/www/html/
   ```

3. Configure Nginx for SPA routing:
   ```nginx
   server {
       listen 80;
       server_name your-domain.com;
       root /var/www/html;
       index index.html;

       location / {
           try_files $uri $uri/ /index.html;
       }
   }
   ```

4. Start backend with PM2:
   ```bash
   npm install -g pm2
   cd A3/backend
   FRONTEND_URL=http://your-domain.com pm2 start src/server.js --name stafflink-backend -- 3000
   pm2 save
   pm2 startup
   ```

5. Point the frontend at the backend by setting before building:
   ```bash
   echo "VITE_API_URL=http://your-domain.com:3000" > A3/frontend/.env
   npm run build
   ```

### Option B — Run both locally (simplest)

```bash
# Terminal 1 — Backend
cd A3/backend && npm start

# Terminal 2 — Frontend
cd A3/frontend && npm run dev
```

Visit http://localhost:5173

